  <section class="lp-faq" aria-label="Frequently asked questions">
    <div class="lp-faq__inner">
      <div class="lp-faq__head">
        <p class="lp-faq__eyebrow bbi-mono">Common questions</p>
        <h2>What buyers ask about ergoCentric.</h2>
        <p class="lp-faq__cta">Still have a question? <a href="tel:18008359565">Call 1&#8209;800&#8209;835&#8209;9565</a> or <a href="/pages/quote">request a quote</a> and we&rsquo;ll respond in 1 business day.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lp-faq__list">

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">01</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Where are ergoCentric chairs made?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>ergoCentric manufactures all chairs in Concord, Ontario. The factory has operated in Canada since the company was founded, and all components are sourced and assembled domestically. This means shorter lead times than imported alternatives and post-sale service that doesn&rsquo;t require cross-border coordination.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">02</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">What is the warranty on ergoCentric chairs?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>ergoCentric provides a 12-year warranty on mechanisms &mdash; the longest in the industry for task seating. Frame and cylinder warranties are also among the longest in the category. As your authorized dealer, Brant Business Interiors handles all warranty claims; you call us, and we coordinate directly with the Concord factory to resolve the issue.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">03</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">What makes a chair suitable for 24/7 use?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>ergoCentric&rsquo;s 24/7 line is engineered and tested for continuous multi-shift use &mdash; meaning the same chair is used by rotating staff with no rest period. The mechanism is rated for higher cycle counts, the foam is denser and recovers faster, and structural components are reinforced for cumulative load. Standard task chairs are rated for single-occupant, single-shift use and will degrade faster under multi-shift conditions.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">04</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Are ergoCentric chairs available under OECM?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes. Brant Business Interiors is an OECM Supplier Partner (Agreement 2025-470) and ergoCentric products are included in our OECM catalogue. Ontario institutional buyers can purchase directly from us without re-tendering. Reference &ldquo;OECM Agreement 2025-470&rdquo; on your purchase order and we&rsquo;ll include it on the invoice.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">05</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Can I trial ergoCentric chairs before committing to a large order?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
